  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Furnishing of Primary School and Provision of Scholarships to Displaced Students</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After the earthquake, roughly 5,000 people from Port-au-Prince and Jacmel moved to Ansi-a-Petri. Our Lady of Lourdes Primary School could not physically accommodate the new students from displaced families. The extra students were taught in improvised outdoor classrooms that were unsuitable for learning, especially during the rainy season. The Canadian government funded the construction of a new Our Lady of Lourdes Primary School that also functions as a hurricane shelter.  JRS purchased 600 desks so the students could learn in a dignified fashion. We also funded 100 scholarships for the children of displaced families. Each $250 scholarship pays for a student&#x2019;s annual fees, uniform, and supplies.</narrative>
  </description>
